Description:   Job Title 14113.Business Development Representative IV.SALES.BUSDEV.IC4   Location HOME-07059-NJ-1   Organization Name Embedded Global Business Unit (EGBU)   Department Description      Oracles Embedded Global Business Unit (EGBU) is a specialized sales team focused on selling and promoting the use of Oracle technology embedded inside devices and systems. We specialize in selling databases and middleware into a partners products under the Embedded Site License (ESL).Examples of devices and systems that currently embed Oracle technology include:BMWin car systems,Motorolasmartphones, Google search appliances,CiscoVoIP switches,RSAsecurity appliances,EMCstorage solutions,Siemensmedical systems, and many more.   Brief Description      Oracles Embedded Global Business Unit is looking for a senior business development representative who has a passion for researching worldwide industry trends and identifying target embedded applications. It is critical for candidates to work well with other teams and to have a strong leadership presence. Candidates must have a proven ability to understand industry trends, create action plans to capitalize on them, and convince senior management as well as sales teams across the world.   The position is a member of the business and strategy development team inside Oracles Global Embedded Business Unit and reports to the Director of Business and Strategy Development. This position is available near major airports in North America,Europeand Asia Pacific and requires the ability to travel internationally up to 50% of the time.   Detailed Description        Job Requirements        Additional Details      Responsibilities: .    Performs market segmentation and analysis in industries where Oracle has a limited embedded presence to identify key applications to target. .    Executes aggressive strategies and sales enablement plans to successfully drive embedded product sales, including developing presentations, applications notes, customer success stories, and prospect lists. .    Provides sales team with information on Oracle value proposition, specific industry needs Oracle can address, and assists in making a compelling case to prospects. .    Acts as primary liaison between Sales, Sales Consulting, Product Marketing, and Industry Business Units. .    Regularly attends customer sales meetings and events. .    Provides subject matter expertise to external communication efforts working with PR and AR.

Preferred Qualifications: .     5+ years experience working as business development representative or industry/marketing analysts; Knowledge of Oracle products and competition, especially database technology a plus. .    Must possess industry knowledge relevant to embedded opportunities and proven ability to perform market analysis and segmentation; Prior employment with related embedded software vendor a plus. .    Experience in one of the following industries: Healthcare, Life Sciences, High Technology or Manufacturing. .    Logical, analytical thinking with proven record substantiating findings and recommendations. .    Demonstrable track record providing direction and mentoring others in person and remotely. .    Experience working in non-routine and very complex environments, involving the application of advanced technical/business skills. .    Solid understanding of software sales, especially embedded industries and practices. .    Detail-oriented and organized with the ability to self-prioritize based on objectives. .    BA/BS degree in related field; Masters and advanced degrees in related field a plus. .    Fluent in English with strong written and verbal skills; Proficiency in other languages a plus.             Location Warren, NJ, US

